SIMPLE: treacherous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Treacherous
<hw>Treach"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Treacher</er>.]</ety> <def>Like a traitor; involving treachery;
violating allegiance or faith pledged; traitorous to the state or
sovereign; perfidious in private life; betraying a trust;
faithless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Loyal father of a <qex>treacherous</qex> son.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>treacherous</qex> smile, a mask for secret hate.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Faithless; perfidious; traitorous; false;
insidious; plotting.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Treach"er*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Treach"er*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treachery</ent>⟦br⟧
